<subSubSection id="9983A9D91B0AFFC6FD48F478FD53F72C" pageId="20" pageNumber="531" type="description">
<paragraph id="D126FA521B0AFFC6FD48F478FD53F72C" blockId="20.[732,1325,1664,2090]" lastBlockId="20.[120,1325,2097,2604]" pageId="20" pageNumber="531">
<emphasis id="E3ED26401B0AFFC6FD48F478FC4EF7F6" bold="true" box="[732,990,2057,2090]" pageId="20" pageNumber="531">Descriptive notes.</emphasis>
Head-body 162 mm, tail 76 mm, hindfoot 30 mm,all measurements from the holotype (young adult male). No specific data are available for body weight. Foch’s Tuco-tuco is small-sized. General color is drab buffy brown, with ventral hairs washed with paler tones; hairs are slate at bases. Muzzle and crown are nearly black. Skull is similar to the Cordoba Tuco-tuco (C. bergr) but shows bullae evenly inflated.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
